content.text:
Hello! I'm ready to help you explore the codebase and design implementation plans.

I can see this is a git repository with some recent changes. To get started effectively, I should understand what this project is about and what you'd like me to work on.

Could you please share:
1. What requirements or features you'd like me to design a plan for?
2. Any specific perspective or approach you'd like me to take?

In the meantime, let me get a quick overview of the project structure to understand what we're working with.

<function_calls>
<invoke name="bash">
<parameter name="command">ls -la /app</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>
<invoke name="bash">
<parameter name="command">find /app -name "package.json" -o -name "README.md" | head -10</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>
<invoke name="bash">
<parameter name="command">cat /app/package.json 2>/dev/null || echo "No package.json in root"</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

This will help me understand the project context before diving into your specific requirements.
